{"type":"message","id":"ea5b59df","parentId":"a91ca0c7","timestamp":"2026-04-15T01:05:03.735Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the sessions:\n\n1. `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status to Lead) - **running** - this is the current cron session I'm in, started at 1776215067467 (~1 second ago)\n2. `cron:ed2d0b5d` (5p Progress Report - QLHV) - **running** - started at 1776214290785 → running for ~12.9 minutes (from 00:51 to 01:04)\n3. `cron:6f3323ef` (5p Progress Report - DTLX) - **running** - started at 1776199558073 → running for ~9h 15m (from ~23:13 UTC to 01:04 UTC)\n\n\n4. `telegram:direct:6053576134` (Lead direct) - **running** - but the updatedAt timestamp (1776214605488) suggests it may have ended and restarted, since the original runtime was 535 seconds, though there's some inconsistency in how the timing is recorded\n5. `telegram:group:-5163901258` - still checking this one\n\n, but the updatedAt of 1776214467822 shows it's been running for about 10 minutes since the last activity\n6. `main` - marked as done, so it's not currently active\n\nLooking at the 6 sessions I found, I'm filtering out the ones that are actually still running. The cron jobs are definitely active, and the Telegram sessions show recent updates, so those count. The main session being done means it's not part of the active count.\n\nI need to exclude the cron:e7885813 session since that's what I'm currently in, leaving me with 5 other active sessions to report on.\n\nFor the timing on those sessions, I'm calculating how long they've been running based on their start times. The cron:ed2d0b5d session started around 00:51 UTC and is still going, so that's roughly 13 minutes. The cron:6f3323ef one started much earlier, around 23:13 UTC yesterday, making it about 9 hours and 11 minutes total.\n\nNow looking at the telegram:direct:6053576134 session - it started at 00:35 UTC and last updated at 00:36 UTC, which means it's been running for about 29 minutes, though I'm seeing conflicting data points in the session details that I need to reconcile.\n\nFor the cron:6f3323ef session, the timestamps are clearer - it started at 23:13 UTC on April 14th and has been running for roughly 9 hours 51 minutes. Now I'm compiling the full status report across all the cron jobs: three of them are actively running with their respective durations, and I'm also noting the telegram:direct:6053576134 session as another active component in this system.\n\nI'm also tracking a few completed sessions that ended normally as expected - the main session wrapped up at 00:46 UTC, and the daily briefing cron finished around 23:16 UTC. There's a telegram group session that I'm still calculating the duration for.","thinkingSignature":"4f6f961d684dd1d95c9bb59a437b359cee03a68e0d8292c696b618c9a8ffa83c"},{"type":"text","text":"I can see the sessions. Excluding the current cron session (`cron:e7885813`), there are 5 other active sessions. Sending the status report to Lead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_satqvhij0xt1_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 01:04 UTC 15 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 5\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p): running — 5p progress monitor — ~13m\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p): running — 5p progress monitor DTLX — ~9h 51m\n• cron:e7885813 (Status): running — Agent Status to Lead — now\n• telegram:direct:6053576134 (Lead): running — direct comm channel — ~29m\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (Group): running — group monitoring — ~10m\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: none\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":8588,"output":926,"cacheRead":13849,"cacheWrite":303,"totalTokens":23666,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestam